<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-16T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-16T16:00:00-05:00" n="1005" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1005">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 860d.00/300</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé in Sweden</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WS1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Whitehouse</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-16T17:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">October
                                            16, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1215. Your 2985, October 12, 5 p.m. While fears for the consequences
                                which would follow withdrawal of enemy troops may be well founded,
                                at the same time in investigating and reporting further on this
                                question, bear in mind that Department has confidential information
                                to show that Germany is instigating requests for protection by
                                German troops on the same pretexts.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_LR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>